Code review complete. I've identified **3 bugs** in `middleware/wrap_writer.go`:

1. **httpFancyWriter.Flush() (line 118-121)**: Doesn't call `maybeWriteHeader()`, so `Status()` returns 0 instead of 200 when Flush is called before any Write/WriteHeader

2. **http2FancyWriter.Flush() (line 154-157)**: Same issue as #1

3. **httpFancyWriter.ReadFrom() (line 132)**: Double-counts bytes when `tee` is set, since `io.Copy` already increments bytes through `Write()` calls, then line 132 adds the total again

All three bugs affect response metadata tracking but don't corrupt the actual HTTP response sent to clients. They're Medium severity issues affecting monitoring/logging.

Detailed findings saved to `/sessions/quirky-practical-cerf/mnt/QPB/benchmarks/run_001/chi/haiku/code_reviews/CHI-06_review.md`
